HEADWORD: Kamtschadales
<hw>Kam"tscha*dales</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[from the
older spelling <ets>Kamtschatka</ets> for Kamchatka.]</ety>
<fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>An aboriginal tribe inhabiting the southern
part of the Kamchatka peninsula; called also
<altname>Kamchadals</altname> and <altname>Itelmen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
